  <title>Decimal Mark</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Decimal Mark</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Decimal Mark or Separator</text> is the generic term for the symbol used to separate the integer part from the fractional part of a number when it is written in decimal form.</para>
          <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:0px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:0px;">In the UK it is a &apos;.&apos; - also called a stop, or a period</li>
            <li styleclass="Popup Box" style="margin-left:0px;">In Europe it is a &apos;,&apos; - also called a comma</li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
